Summary: This chunk lists the methods for managing editor settings, shortcuts, favorites, and project metadata, and details the signal emitted when a setting changes.

Methods
* Method: add_property_info(info: Dictionary) -> void
* Method: add_shortcut(path: String, shortcut: Shortcut) -> void
* Method: check_changed_settings_in_group(setting_prefix: String) -> bool
* Method: erase(property: String) -> void
* Method: get_changed_settings() -> PackedStringArray
* Method: get_favorites() -> PackedStringArray
* Method: get_project_metadata(section: String, key: String, default: Variant = null) -> Variant
* Method: get_recent_dirs() -> PackedStringArray
* Method: get_setting(name: String) -> Variant
* Method: get_shortcut(path: String) -> Shortcut
* Method: get_shortcut_list() -> PackedStringArray
* Method: has_setting(name: String) -> bool
* Method: has_shortcut(path: String) -> bool
* Method: is_shortcut(path: String, event: InputEvent) -> bool
* Method: mark_setting_changed(setting: String) -> void
* Method: remove_shortcut(path: String) -> void
* Method: set_builtin_action_override(name: String, actions_list: Array[InputEvent]) -> void
* Method: set_favorites(dirs: PackedStringArray) -> void
* Method: set_initial_value(name: StringName, value: Variant, update_current: bool) -> void
* Method: set_project_metadata(section: String, key: String, data: Variant) -> void
* Method: set_recent_dirs(dirs: PackedStringArray) -> void
* Method: set_setting(name: String, value: Variant) -> void

Signals
Signal: settings_changed()
Emitted after any editor setting has changed.
